						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near a well called <hi rend="italic">Mālabhāvi,</hi> about 1/4 km to the north-east of the village.</p>						

						<p>PARĀBHAVA.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year, Parābhava, Āshāḍha, śu. 11.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the digging of two wells in the village Gaṇḍḍiganumulu by Rāja Timmā reḍḍi for the merit of his parents Basivireḍi and Aṁkamasāni. The inscription was engraved by Pedamallayya of Sathanapalli.</p>						

						</summary>
